<subSubSection id="E6E6C631D8D62B3CCD2B24867A394E14" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5F0C429F288ECEF430A5C2A6DBEF6150" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A569C676955C563635783A76B6F0A889" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Mexico (Oaxaca), in oak, oak-pine, and pine forest, typically found in anthropogenically disturbed habitats such as roadsides, pastures, old fields and corn fields, 2100-2900 m in elevation (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="37953F3CA7E264B7B70DAA88CDA7F43A" captionStart="Figure 71" captionStartId="F71" captionText="Figure 71. Map of geographic distribution of L. moziniana var. oaxacana based on herbarium specimen data." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.168.51904.figure71" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/480083" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">71</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
